PRESTIGE CLASSES
For the 3.5e Open Game License
PRESTIGE CLASSES
INTRODUCTION
This document details the prestige classes adapted for the Oreka: Echoes of the Elemental Dawn
roleplaying setting. Each class is presented with its full mechanics, including stats, abilities, and
level progression, as defined in the Open Game License (OGL). The classes are flavored to align
with Oreka's elemental themes, Kin cultures, and historical events, such as the Deceivers' War, the
Shattering of Man, and the rise of the Ascended Gods.
Part I contains the fifteen OGL-adapted prestige classes drawn from the D&D 3.5 Edition core
rules, each reimagined for Oreka's world. Part II presents the Oreka-original prestige classes:
unique paths born from the setting's elemental magic, Kin cultures, and the legacies of war and
harmony.
PART I
OGL-Adapted Prestige Classes

Prestige Classes
79
Arcane Archer
Arcane Archers are revered among the Hasura and Pasua Elves, whose airy magic and mastery of
the Great Forests' longbows make them ideal candidates. These archers weave wind-based spells
into their arrows, striking with precision from treetop perches. Post-Shattering, they protect Elven
enclaves from Human incursions, their arrows carrying the Wind Lord's essence.
Requirements
• Race: Elf (Hasura, Pasua, Kovaka, Na'wasua) or half-elf.
• Base Attack Bonus: +6.
• Feats: Point Blank Shot, Precise Shot, Weapon Focus (longbow or shortbow), Elemental
Affinity (Air) in Oreka.
• Spells: Ability to cast 1st-level arcane spells.
Class Features
• Hit Die: d8.
• Class Skills: Craft (Int), Hide (Dex), Listen (Wis), Move Silently (Dex), Ride (Dex), Spot (Wis),
Survival (Wis), Use Rope (Dex) (4 + Int modifier skill points/level).
• Weapon and Armor Proficiency: All simple and martial weapons, light and medium armor,
shields (except tower shields).
