• Phase Arrow (Sp): 1/day, arrow passes through nonmagical barriers, negating cover,
concealment, and armor (6th). Standard action.
• Hail of Arrows (Sp): 1/day, fire one arrow per arcane archer level at targets within range,
using primary attack bonus (8th).
• Arrow of Death (Sp): Create an arrow (1 day), forcing a DC 20 Fortitude save or death on hit
(10th). One arrow at a time, lasts 1 year.
Oreka Integration
Hasura Arcane Archers imbue arrows with air spells (e.g., fog cloud), while Pasua use charm
effects. Their Elemental Affinity (Air) feat enhances wind-based spells, and they guard Great
Forests' borders, wary of Taraf-Imro Humans.
Arcane Trickster
Arcane Tricksters are rare, blending rogue stealth with arcane magic, often distrusted as
"Deceivers" among the Kin. Pekakarlik Dwarves and Halflings, skilled in river navigation, adopt
this path to outwit trade rivals along the Great River. Their magic, tied to water or air, aids their
subterfuge, though they face cultural stigma.
Requirements
• Alignment: Any nonlawful.
• Skills: Decipher Script 7 ranks, Disable Device 7 ranks, Escape Artist 7 ranks, Knowledge
(arcana) 4 ranks.
• Spells: Ability to cast mage hand and one 3rd-level arcane spell.
• Special: Sneak attack +2d6.
Class Features
• Hit Die: d4.
• Class Skills: Appraise (Int), Balance (Dex), Bluff (Cha), Climb (Str), Concentration (Con),
Craft (Int), Decipher Script (Int), Diplomacy (Cha), Disable Device (Int), Disguise (Cha),
Escape Artist (Dex), Gather Information (Cha), Hide (Dex), Jump (Str), Knowledge (Int),
Listen (Wis), Move Silently (Dex), Open Lock (Dex), Profession (Wis), Sense Motive (Wis),
Search (Int), Sleight of Hand (Dex), Speak Language (Int), Spellcraft (Int), Spot (Wis), Swim
(Str), Tumble (Dex), Use Rope (Dex) (4 + Int modifier skill points/level).
• Weapon and Armor Proficiency: No new proficiencies.
