Prestige Classes
97
• Improved Ally: Diplomacy check reduces planar ally payment by 50% if creature shares
alignment.
• Augment Summoning: Gain feat (2nd).
• Extended Summoning: Double duration of summoning spells (3rd).
• Contingent Conjuration: Prepare a summoning/calling spell as contingency (4th).
• Planar Cohort: Call a creature as a cohort, 1,000 gp × HD, ECL = character level –2 (5th).
Oreka Integration
Nawasua Thaumaturgists summon air elementals, Eruskan water elementals, using Riverborn to
negotiate with river spirits. Their Planar Cohort might be a River Serpent, guarding Great River
settlements from Deceiver rifts.
PART II
“Oreka-Original Prestige Classes”
Elemental Savant
A master of a single element, the Elemental Savant gains enhanced spells tied to their chosen
element. Rarozhki Dwarves often specialize in fire, while Eruskan Humans favor water, and
Hasura Elves attune to air. The Savant's devotion to a single elemental force grants them
unparalleled mastery within their domain, making them formidable channelers of Oreka's primal
energies.
Requirements
• Spells: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.
• Feats: Elemental Affinity feat.
• Skills: Knowledge (Arcana) 8 ranks.
Class Features
• Hit Die: d4.
• Class Skills: Concentration (Con), Craft (Int), Knowledge (arcana, nature) (Int), Profession
(Wis), Spellcraft (Int) (2 + Int modifier skill points/level).
• Weapon and Armor Proficiency: No new proficiencies.

