• Elemental Focus: Cast elemental spells of chosen element at +1 caster level (1st), increasing
to +2 (3rd).
• Resistance: Gain resistance 10 to chosen element's energy type (2nd).
• Elemental Mastery: Elemental spells of chosen type gain +1 to save DCs (4th).
• Immunity: Gain immunity to chosen element's energy type (5th).
Oreka Integration
Rarozhki Fire Savants channel the Lord of Flame's essence through embersteel forges, while
Eruskan Water Savants draw upon the Lady of the Sea's tides. Their focused mastery makes them
invaluable in campaigns where elemental forces shape the battlefield.
River Warden
Pekakarlik Dwarves often become River Wardens, protectors of Oreka's waterways. They blend
combat and water magic, standing sentinel over the Great River and its tributaries. River Wardens
are respected guardians of trade routes and communities that depend on the flowing waters for
survival.
Requirements
• Skills: Swim 5 ranks, Knowledge (Nature) 5 ranks.

Prestige Classes
99
• Spells: Ability to cast water breathing.
Class Features
• Hit Die: d8.
• Class Skills: Craft (Int), Handle Animal (Cha), Heal (Wis), Knowledge (nature, geography)
(Int), Listen (Wis), Profession (Wis), Ride (Dex), Spot (Wis), Survival (Wis), Swim (Str) (4 + Int
modifier skill points/level).
• Weapon and Armor Proficiency: All simple and martial weapons, light and medium armor,
shields.
