• Sacred Forge: Consecrate a forge, granting +2 to Craft checks for enchanted items.
• Fire Imbue: Imbue a weapon with +1d4 fire damage for 1 hour, usable 1/day per level (1st).
• Embersteel Tempering: Reduce crafting time for embersteel items by 25% and add +1
hardness (2nd).

Prestige Classes
101
• Channel Flame: Channel divine energy as a 30-ft. cone of fire, 3d6 damage (Reflex DC 10 +
level + Wis for half), usable 1/day (3rd).
• Greater Imbue: Imbue weapons with +1d6 fire damage and the flaming burst property for 1
hour (4th).
• Forge Avatar: 1/day, assume a form wreathed in sacred fire for 1 minute: +4 Str, +4 Con, fire
resistance 30, melee attacks deal +2d6 fire damage (5th).
Oreka Integration
Forge Mystics are the spiritual heart of Rarozhki smithing culture. In Kharazhad, they maintain
the great forges where embersteel is worked, and their creations are sought by warriors across
Oreka. Their Channel Flame ability echoes the Lord of Flame's gift to the Thirdborn.
Wind Dancer
Mytroan Humans or Pasua Elves often take this path, enhancing their speed and air magic in
combat. Wind Dancers move like living gales, their footwork a blend of martial art and arcane
expression. They channel the Wind Lord's breath through every step and strike.
Requirements
• Dexterity: 15.
• Skills: Perform (Dance) 5 ranks.
• Feats: Wind Step feat.
Class Features
• Hit Die: d8.
• Class Skills: Balance (Dex), Escape Artist (Dex), Jump (Str), Listen (Wis), Move Silently (Dex),
Perform (Cha), Spot (Wis), Tumble (Dex) (4 + Int modifier skill points/level).
• Weapon and Armor Proficiency: All simple weapons, light armor; no shields.
Abilities and Progression
Level BAB Fort Ref Will Special
1st +0 +0 +2 +2 Zephyr Step (+10 ft. movement)
2nd +1 +0 +3 +3 Gust Strike
3rd +2 +1 +3 +3 Wind's Embrace
4th +3 +1 +4 +4 Swift Casting (air spells)
5th +3 +1 +4 +4 Tempest Dance
• Zephyr Step: +10 ft. to base movement speed, +20 ft. when unarmored (1st).

OREKA — Echoes of the Elemental Dawn
102
• Gust Strike: 1/day per level, add 1d6 wind damage to a melee attack and push the target 5 ft.
(Reflex DC 10 + level + Dex negates push) (2nd).
• Wind's Embrace: Feather fall at will on self; +4 to Balance and Jump checks (3rd).
• Swift Casting: Cast air-based spells like gust of wind as a swift action 1/day (4th).
• Tempest Dance: 1/day, enter a whirling dance for 1 minute: all enemies within 10 ft. must
make Reflex saves (DC 10 + level + Dex) each round or be knocked prone; allies gain +2
dodge to AC (5th).
Oreka Integration
Wind Dancers are celebrated performers and warriors among the Pasua and Mytroan, often
appearing at festivals like the Starweave. In battle, their Tempest Dance can turn the tide against
massed enemies, embodying the Wind Lord's untamed freedom.
Golden Cantor
Golden Cantors are bard-warriors who weave enchantment and song into instruments of justice
and unity. Born from the traditions of the Anacrusis and the songs of Hareem, they swear oaths to
protect the bonds between Kin and punish those who betray them. Their golden-toned voices carry
supernatural power.
Requirements
• Skills: Perform (Sing) 8 ranks, Knowledge (history) 4 ranks.
• Feats: Elemental Affinity (Air).
• Spells: Ability to cast 1st-level arcane spells.
• Special: Bardic music class feature.
Class Features
• Hit Die: d8.
• Class Skills: Bluff (Cha), Concentration (Con), Craft (Int), Diplomacy (Cha), Gather
Information (Cha), Knowledge (history, nobility) (Int), Perform (Cha), Sense Motive (Wis),
Spellcraft (Int) (4 + Int modifier skill points/level).
• Weapon and Armor Proficiency: All simple weapons, rapier, short sword; light armor.
