• Golden Voice (Su): Singing supercharges enchantment spells and bardic music with golden
overtones, granting +1 to save DCs of mind-affecting effects while performing.
• Kin's Harmony (Su): Aura that inspires unity among Kin, granting allies within 30 ft. a +2
morale bonus to Diplomacy and Sense Motive checks, and imposing –2 on Intimidate checks
made against them. Save DC: 10 + Golden Cantor level + Cha modifier.
• Vengeful Strike (Ex): A precise, punishing strike that deals extra damage (Golden Cantor
level + Cha modifier) to betrayers, oath-breakers, and those who harm allies. Usable a
number of times per day equal to Golden Cantor level + Cha modifier (2nd).
• Song of Betrayal (Sp): A haunting performance that punishes traitors and those who shatter
bonds of trust. Single-target or small-area debuff; DC based on Cha (3rd).
• Greater Golden Voice: +2 to save DCs of mind-affecting effects while performing (replaces
Golden Voice bonus) (4th).
• Anthem of the Unbroken: 1/day, a powerful song that grants all allies within 60 ft. immunity
to fear and compulsion effects for 1 minute and heals 2d8+level HP (5th).
Oreka Integration
Golden Cantors serve as the moral voice of the Anacrusis and as diplomats in fractured Kin
relations. Kethren Vale, "The Broken Measure," is the most famous living Golden Cantor, wielding
his cracked voice and rapier to defend Oreka's bonds of trust.
